{
  "texts": [
    "Besides, m represents the diagonal length of the bounding box that encloses both the predicted frame and the real frame, α denotes the weight coefficient, IoU represents the intersection over union, which calculates the ratio of the intersection area to the union area of the predicted and real frames' bounding boxes.",
    "v represents the aspect ratio difference between the predicted box and the real box.",
    "The proposed method was evaluated on three publicly available steel surface defect detection datasets that are widely used in the field of object detection: NEU-DET, GC10-DET and APDDD datasets.",
    "Through extensive experiments, this paper demonstrates the soundness, effectiveness, and superiority of the experimental design for the improved YOLOv5s.",
    "In this study, the experiment was carried out using the PyTorch deep learning framework, and the environment was set up on a Windows 10 operating system."
  ]
}